name: La Condesa
bio: Two-times James Beard-nominated Mexican restaurant in downtown Austin, Texas. Est. 2009.

social_posts.post_text:
MEZCAL MIÉRCOLES

Every Wednesday through the end of the year, enjoy 1/2 price mezcal pours & cocktails all day long featuring some of our favorite makers.

Today’s feature: Cinco Sentidos! Stop by for pours of @5sentidosagave’s Espadín-Tobaziche, Tobalá, Sierra Negra & Papalometl varietals, and learn just how these makers craft their spirits. 

If cocktails are more your vibe, let our bartenders whip you up a one-of-a-kind specialty featuring Cinco Sentidos mezcal with flavors of raspberry, orange & cardamom.

Order up!

A new month means a new torta, and we’re ending 2022 with one hell of a sando. 

STEAK MILANESA — shishito chimi, dos lunas, smashed avocado
Not just a yes but a HELL yes. The cutest little sopes you ever did see — cauliflower chorizo, black beans & escabeche.

MEZCAL MIÉRCOLES 

Still going extra strong with your mid-week mezcal pick-me-ups, and today is no different. Stop by and enjoy half-priced pours and cocktails using our featured mezcals. Today’s mezcal: Oaxaca’s own @creadorspirits 

CREADOR LUMBRE: angustifolia agave with flavors of bubble gum, cola, & sweet apple with a vegetal finish

CREADOR JABALÌ: convallis agave with flavors of white pepper, clay, pine & other woods

CREADOR MEXICANO: rhodacantha agave with flavors of leather, honey & clove

CREADOR BARRIL: karwinskii agave with flavors of sandalwood, vanilla & honey with fruit notes on the nose

Your Monday reminder to eat more green food.

Treat your friends & fam to a gift card so they can follow suit. Link in bio!

Wild out on your Wednesday — Mezcal Miércoles is back, baby! Today’s feature: @nuestrasoledad.mezcal. Sip it neat or sit back and let your bartender whip you up something *magical.*

Mezcal Nuestra Soledad is a Oaxaca-made mezcal showcasing the difference between 4 Oaxacan villages in both flavor profile and culture. This mezcal is born from ancient tradition and hand-crafted to conserve & retain the centuries-old methods of cultivating and producing this “elixir of the gods.” Up to bat today:

Ejutla: flavors of white flowers, roasted chiles & earthen minerals. Long finish with wood smoke. 

Lachiquì: flavors of fresh cherries, cedar wood & cigar box with a peppery green kick. A long, earthy finish. 

Matalàn: flavors of roasted plantain, smoked meats, toasted cacao nibs with a citrus & woody finish. 

Zoquitlàn: flavors of lemon zest, tropical fruit & smoked game with a big & complex palate featuring honeysuckle & sandalwood. Exotic finish with nuanced with lychee & savory herbs.

Found your weekend plans. Drool-worthy specials at your service, starting today until they’re gone!

ALBÓNDIGAS — pork & beef meatballs, guajillo broth, rajas & house-made telera 

GRINGA AL PASTOR — bacon fat flour tortilla, pork shoulder, pineapple pico & @doslunascheese 

CRUDO — hiramasa, big eye tuna, lemon & fennel

The only thing better than tamales during the holidays is — well, absolutely nothing. Run, don’t walk, over to Chef Rick’s new feature with @madein and see just exactly how Chef works his magic with these beautiful & traditional holiday treats. Link in bio!
Our New Year’s resolution? Drink more bubbles.

Join us for bubbles, special offerings and *immaculate vibes* as we bring this year to a close. 2022 was pretty damn good to us, and we’re raising our glasses to 2023 all night long. Link in bio to make your NYE dinner reservation.
Everything we do is rooted in love. Our heart on our sleeve via art on our exterior by @cruzortizart.

¡Brunch! Every Saturday & Sunday from 11a-2p.

See our menu & lock in those weekend plans early at link in bio.

James Beard-nominated 2010 > James Beard-nominated 2023. 

The Outstanding Restaurant award means a lot to us, because it honors the culmination of every single effort made by those who have been a part of La Condesa these 14 years.

We are incredibly thankful for this honor, and grateful to our team — past and present — who always strive to make it better than the day before.

This Sunday, join us for a special Galentine’s Day edition of our “All Tequila, All Shade” Drag Brunch series, presented by @tequilatromba and @doshombres & benefiting @equality_alliance.

Ticketed reservations are a must at $25/person, and include access to the show and our extra espicy clack fan. 

Link in bio to join us gals, gays & pals — all are welcome ❤️

Swipe to meet our talented lineup of drag artists!

We’re 14 this month, so we invited over friends & alum from @tryhardcoffee for not one, but two brunch parties this weekend 2/25-2/26, with collab drink & food specials, DJ Dana Scully of @queervinylco spinning and a portion of sales dedicated to the Perez Family Farm in Huehuetenango, Guatamala. 

📸: @shelbysorrel

Extending a royal welcome to the Reina Del Sur - vodka, dry curacao, absinthe, house-made jalapeño grenadine. *princess wave*⁠
⁠
A new addition featured on our Spring cocktail menu. ⁠

Gracias, Austin: We’re nominated for Restaurant of the Year at this year’s CultureMap Tastemaker Awards.⁠
⁠
Cross your fingers and join us for the unveiling of the winners 5/11 at Fair Market — link in bio for details.⁠

We're serving drag with a side of brunch - and you're invited. 🌮🥂💄 It’s a special Cinco de Mayo edition of La Condesa’s “All Tequila, All Shade” Drag Brunch, presented by @tequilatromba and @doshombres.⁠
⁠
A portion of proceeds from the drink specials will benefit @equality_alliance and this time, donations will be generously matched by Tequila Tromba and Dos Hombres Mezcal. ⁠
⁠
Tickets can be found at the link in bio. All ways, all welcomed. See y'all there! 🪩

Calling all foodies, cocktail connoisseurs and all-knowing Austinites - nominations are open for @austin_monthly's Best of ATX 2023 now, until 5/21. It's up to you, so go loco. ⁠
⁠
To nominate La Condesa for all things 'Best', head to the link in our bio!
We saved you a seat. 🌮 Join us for happy hour every weekday, 5-6p. 1/2 off all things boozy, bubbly & brewed. Reserve your table at the link in bio. 🍹
HAUTE VEG SUMMER 🥒🥕🥬 Crudité - cold Texas veggies, skordalia, lemon, olive oil. Here through the weekend. 🔥

Happy hour just got happier at La Condesa. 🔥🌮☀️ From 5-6p every weekday, come get $3 a la carte tacos at the bar! Choose from pollo, carnitas, cachete or hongos and pair it with a 1/2 off boozy bev. 🍻 Order one, order 10 - they are yours for the taking. 

Our bar and bar patio is on a walk-in basis. Claim your seat and beat the heat this summer! 🇲🇽

#atxhappyhour #lacondesaaustin

Pulling up to happy hour like: 🤠🌮🍹⁠
⁠
1/2 off all alcohol + $3 taco specials at the bar/bar patio, every weekday from 5-6p. ☀️

🎨: @cruzortizart

On Friday, the youth leaders of @urbanrootsatx spent the day with us at La Condesa as they prepared five delicious, farm fresh dishes to serve to their community and family members. 🌱🍅🥕 From hand picked flowers, to savory chicken wings, to sweet tres leches - it was a day to remember. 👩‍🌾🧑‍🌾👨‍🌾

We’re proud to continue supporting Urban Roots and their mission to achieving a thriving food system cultivated by youth and community. Thank you for all you do! 🤍

#sustainability #urbanroots #farmfresh

We’re kicking off Summer of Ceviche 2023 on the beach in Baja California. ☀️🐟 Known for their fresh seafood and sunny weather - these dishes are bringing all of the bright, salty and hot flavors. 🍉🌊🌶️

San Felipe by Chef Frank:
morita, arbol, tomatillo, avocado puree, cucumbers, shishitos, watermelon radish

La Chorera by Chef Cody:
garlic and lime marinated clams, honeydew cucumber mint broth, pickled onions, serrano oil

Mexicali by Chef Edgar:
avocado puree, pickles, watermelon broth, fried onion, nasturtium flowers

Sorbet by Chef Abigail:
texas watermelon, tajin

Isla Sandia:
pisco, chareau, acho reyes, watermelon, lime

Available today-July 4th! 🔥 #summerofceviche #lacondesaaustin #freshfish

Truly happy as a clam. ⁠
⁠
Summer of Ceviche at La Condesa means 4 months of ceviche especiales, inspired by five various regions of Mexico. 📍Baja California sounds like waves crashing on the beach and tastes like fresh, garlic + lime marinated clams. 🪸Travel with us, no passport needed.
The most important meal of the weekend - brunch. 🥂🍊 Chilaquiles, summer squash, mimosas by the bottle y so much mas. Saturdays/Sundays, starting at 11a. Reserve your table at the link in our bio!

"Jalisco es México" 🇲🇽 We've made it to the second stop of our Summer of Ceviche trip. Known for its mariachi, tequila, ranchera music and sombreros - Jalisco is one of the most popular destinations in Mexico. ⁠
⁠
In this ceviche rotation we have the 'Tlaquepaque' made by Chef Frank: sole, roasted peach + mango puree, pickled peaches, avocado, sugar rush peach peppers. 🍑🥑🌶️ Inspired by peach season here in Texas, Chef Frank combined them with a delicate, sweet fish like sole + avocado as an ode to Jalisco's prominent presence in exportation. The Tlaquepaque is available now-July 18th. 🔥
Tacos de Pescado with pineapple pico + guacamole 🐟️ A Summer of Ceviche especial you don't want to miss. 🔥 Available now-July 18th.

The Folklorico tostada - so good, it will get you dancing. Made with citrus infused shrimp, smoked tomatoes & pickled serrano chili. 🦐 Enjoy it today before we continue on our Summer of Ceviche journey!

Next stop, Guerrero. This Summer of Ceviche rotation is inspired by Acapulco in the 50’s, when Hollywood stars escaped the scene for cocktails + beach clubs. 🍹

The Palmitas: canary rockfish, cucumber aguachile, cucumber, macha, red onion. 🌴 Pair it with the frozen Piña Colada, now we’re ready to party.

More specials to come. Available starting today-August 1st.
The Paleta Pop - arroz con leche, puffed rice, chocolate. A Summer of Ceviche postre special. 🍦

The Diamante 💎 Hiramasa, pineapple, coconut, macha, melon, sesame seeds. The piña colada of ceviche. ⁠
⁠
Available now-August 1st.

The Zihuatanejo: citrus marinated mahi mahi, blackberry mango puree, pickled cantaloupe, watermelon radish, micro cilantro. 🍈⁠
⁠
Inspired by the bronze statue of Acapulco, Chef Cody plated this dish to resemble the life-size, beautiful woman found on a rock in the waters of Playa Madera. 🌊 She represents the busy port of Acapulco in the 1950s and 60s. ⁠
⁠
Available through 8/1 for this Summer of Ceviche rotation.

It’s a special Pride edition of La Condesa’s “All Tequila, All Shade” Drag Brunch, presented by @tequilatromba and @doshombres.⁠
⁠
Join us on August 13th for live spins by @djsupermcn4sty, all of your brunch favorites and our Queens, @vyletteward and @diamonddioratx. Start the party off right by adding on mimosas by the bottle or a margarita pitcher! A portion of proceeds from the drink specials will benefit @equality_alliance whose goal is to generate financial support and visibility for grassroots LGBTQIA+ charities fighting for equality in Central Texas.⁠
⁠
Ticketed reservations are recommended, cost $25/person and include access to the show + a custom clack fan. The show kicks off at 12:15pm. Book your table at the link in our bio, and don’t forget to bring cash to tip your Queens! ⁠

Hola, Barbie! We've officially made it to Yucatan on our Summer of Ceviche journey. Inspired by the pink oceanic waters of Las Coloradas, Chef Cody presents this chamomile + chictana salt tossed tuna with red leche de tigre, grapefruit, serrano peppers and avocado. ⁠
⁠
Available now-August 15th

We’re bringing you into the kitchen for some BTS of Chef Cody’s “Las Coloradas” inspired by the famous pink beach of Yucatan. Sustainably sourced and paired with local produce from Texas - always. 👨‍🍳

#summerofceviche #sustainableseafood

This Sunday, join us for Drag with a side of brunch at our special Pride edition of All Tequila, All Shade! We'll be serving (literally) all of your favorites - steak y eggs, seafood coctel, queso flameado and so much more. 🔥🍳 Book your table today at the link in our bio!⁠
⁠
Queens: @vyletteward + @diamonddioratx ⁠and special guest @sierramykels 
Live spins by: @djsupermcn4sty⁠
Presented by: @tequilatromba + @doshombres⁠
In support of: @equality_alliance⁠
⁠
🌈

With a bright + spicy broth base, the Oxman encompasses 'cenotes' or subterranean lagoons found in Yucatan. Chef Edgar features citrus poached shrimp, xnipek broth, tortilla ash oil, avocado and pineapple as he pays homage to the 10,000 natural swimming caves among the Yucatan peninsula. 🦐🌶️⁠
⁠
Available now-August 15th.⁠
⁠
#summerofceviche #sustainableseafood

100° weather and we still made it rain. 💸 Muchas gracias for everyone coming out (oop!) + celebrating #prideweekend with us at Drag Brunch!⁠
⁠
We couldn't have done it without our sponsors @tequilatromba + @doshombres, our Queens @vyletteward @diamonddioratx @sierramykels, DJ @djsupermcn4sty and of course, @equality_alliance. 🌈 Let's do it again!

The final stop of our Summer of Ceviche journey is Veracruz. Coined as Mexico's vanilla capital and major producer of coffee - this helado is our take on an affogato. ☕️ Housemade vanilla ice cream, chocolate, coffee crumble made by Chef Abigail. 🍨 ⁠
⁠
Available today-September 3rd.

Veracruz is home to the Son Jarocho music style - a blend of Spanish, indigenous and African sound. This ceviche by Chef Cody similarly fuses a melody of flavors with vermilion rockfish, smokey tomato water, olive + caper powder, pickled pearl onion, jalapeño, avocado and cilantro oil. 

Available now-September 3rd.

Strike it big with the "Villa Rica", or the rich village - a Summer of Ceviche cocktail special. Made with 400 conejos, aperol, luxardo and egg white by Bartender Brandi. 🍒 The cherry on top of a long week. ⁠
⁠
Available now-September 3rd.
Steak + eggs. Saturdays + Sundays. Good things come in two's, like you + brunch. Head to the link in bio to see what's cookin' this weekend. 🍳

Fresh masa, made in-house daily. Straight from the mill, to your plate. Taste the difference during happy hour every weekday, 5-6p over $3 taco especiales at the bar. 🌮 ⁠
⁠

@tequilatromba is on a mission to plant + save wild agave plants from going extinct - and you can join the movement. 🌵All you have to do? Enjoy a signature Paloma at La Condesa this month. Giving back never tasted so good. 🍊

In celebration of Hispanic Heritage Month, we teamed up with @lalospirits + @carriquitx for an unforgettable dinner party where Chef Jaime + Chef Rick fused the flavors of South Texas + Mexico City.⁠
⁠
Interested in hosting your next celebration with us? Head to the link in bio to connect with our events team. 🌮🪩 ⁠
⁠
📸: @crissyfish

¡Salud! La Condesa is a finalist for @austinchronicle's Best of Austin Readers Poll for Best Tequila Selection + Best Margarita. We owe it all to our hand squeezed juice program, house-made salts (cactus lemongrass + hibiscus rose to name a few) and of course - the creative geniuses behind the bar who source only the best agave spirits. ⁠
⁠
Dare us to earn your vote? Come give our signature margaritas a try at 1/2 off + see what the hype is all about during happy hour, 5-6p daily. ⁠Link to vote is in our bio.⁠
⁠

On Wednesdays, we drink mezcal. This month’s distiller of choice is Mezcalero — a brand that empowers individual artisans in small distilleries + remote villages. 

Join us on Mezcal Miércoles for half-price pours of Mezcalero, all night long. 🌵

Before heading to ACL, come by for a pre-festival drink at LCA: La Condesa Austin. 🔥 Our brand new cocktail lineup just dropped, featuring the 'Hecho de Elote' - a zero-waste, old fashioned coded libation paying homage to our roots. ⁠
⁠
Accompanying headliners:⁠
🍉 Isla Sand(ia)⁠
🍒 La Bomba⁠
🌿 Jarocho ⁠
⁠
#aclfestival2023⁠

Stairway to heaven — aka, the bar. 🥂

This piece by @coloringatx never gets old. 💙
Whether you're heading to ACL W2 or cruising downtown - join us for half-off all drinks + $3 tacos at the bar during happy hour today, from 5-6p. 🌮

When blending cocktail creation + traditional Al Pastor style, you get the Mirador.

Chile + basil infused mezcal, achiote, grilled pineapple, lime, jalapeño. 🌶️ It’s a #1 seller for a reason.

It’s time for La Condesa’s “All Tequila, All Shade” Drag Brunch, presented by @tequilatromba and @400conejosus Mezcal.⁠
⁠
Join us November 12th for live spins, brunch favorites, margaritas by the pitcher + themed cocktails. A portion of proceeds from the drink specials will benefit @equality_alliance whose goal is to generate financial support and visibility for grassroots LGBTQIA+ charities fighting for equality in Central Texas. 🌈⁠
⁠
Ticketed reservations are required, cost $25/person, include access to the show + a custom clack fan and can be found at the link in bio. The show kicks off at 12:15pm with performances by @vyletteward, @diamonddioratx and special guest @pradahill. Don’t forget to bring cash to tip your Queens!

Chef Rick Lopez + team brought La Condesa to the beautiful backyard of Boggy Creek Farm. 🌾 Thank you to @out_inthefield for connecting local farmers with homegrown purveyors over a wonderful evening spent together. We are so thankful to be a part of this opportunity + hope to see you next year. ⁠
⁠
Host Farmers: Carol Ann Sayles, Tracy Geyer & Jack Geyer |  @boggycreekfarm_atx⁠
Guest Chefs: Rick Lopez | @lacondesaaustin⁠
Guest Wineries: @llanowine
Guest Distillery: @benriach⁠
Photographer: @el_doberino

Sustainably sourced + seasonal ingredients, always. Discover new additions to our dinner menu including the Veracruzana: grilled rockfish with olives, capers and charred tomatoes from Marfa, Texas. Served with housemade tortillas made from corn out of Oaxaca.

IYKYK. These stairs lead to one of Austin's best treasures known as the Flour House - originally built in the 1860’s by the Schneider family as part of a brewery, landmarked today by the Texas Historical Commission. Be a part of history by hosting a private event in the Flour House this holiday season - link in bio to start planning.

From butchering, to grilling, to plating. Our ribeye steaks are sourced exclusively from 44 Farms out of Cameron, Texas. 🥩 It doesn't get much better than 5 generations of family ranching + ethically raised beef. Come try the Carne Asada and taste the quality for yourself. ⁠
⁠
📸: @andrewreiner
Get in the holiday spirit(s) at happy hour - every weekday 'til 6p. Half price all bevs + $3 taco specials at the bar. Reservations bookable at the link in bio. 🌮

Our piece of Mexico City in Austin. ⁠

We are closed tomorrow for the holiday - but will be back Friday. Join us for dinner starting at 5p.

Soak up the rest of the weekend (and alcohol) with huevos rancheros, churro waffles, chilaquiles y so much mas. 🍳 Every Saturday-Sunday at 11a. ⁠

📸: @andrewreiner
